Well, the first house we were in was the one I was born in - then from there - my mother and father moved to another house - which was bigger and they shared it with another family, an - an ex-Naval man and his wife, who had a 
son about the same age as myself. And we kept - we were in that house for some years, until the owner died and the house was sold. Consequently we had to - vacate it. And we had a dickens of a job to find a house, I remember. Eventually, we found a house 
w
hich was in - within about - couple of hundred yards of the house we'd - I was born in. Which was a big house, with a basement. We never liked the house, in fact, we were only there about six months because unfortunately we discovered after we got into th
