 place the place was verminous. Anyway we got out of that and moved to another house the last house we were in - and which - my mother and father were in for over fifty - nearly sixty years - which was the last house we were in and there we - we kept, the
 
rent there was - let me see - about - I think when we first went into it was about twelve and six a week. When we left it - when - mother died it was about fifteen bob I think. But - there was very little - addition to it. It was owned by - a man - who we
 knew very well, he was a very - very good landlord actually. He was the owner of two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7673867\charrsid15017164 confectioners\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
