at in the weeks before Christmas there'd always be the - mixing of the plum pudding, and - dropping in the silver threepenny bits and the little china dolls, which were about - oh about an inch long. We'd all have to have a stir of the pudding, which usua
lly used to be mixed with - some old ale, which father used to have to go and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid920634\charrsid15017164 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
