h
 him. The main one of those of course was the Labour party, they used to have always a wagon drawn up, strange to say, SI can still see the spot where they drew it up because it was - was the end of the public convenience. They always used to have a big -
 silk trade union banner behind. And - there was always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13920496\charrsid15017164 a meeting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
 there, I remember hearing Will Crooks, who of course - was our local M.P. at one time, hear him many times speaking from there. And then you'd have all sorts of other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid920634\charrsid15017164 meetings}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  all round it was a sort of - a speakers corner from Hyde Park, only it wasn't on grass it was on cobble stones.
