\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You didn't have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
No, I never could ride a bicycle. I had many opportunities - my uncle who lived in the same road used to - do quite a little bit of - of business in his spare time in buying up old bicycles and renovating them and selling them. Well I had then plenty of o
pportunities of getting a bicycle, but I could never stop on the thing. I was all right as long as somebody held it. But as soon as they let go I feel off. I had no sense of balance at all. And I never have been able to ride, I couldn't even ride a bicycl
e
 now. I wish I could sometimes. I never have been - it's one of the regrets - I do regret not being able to do it. But - again it was not - I never used to worry about it very much, really. I - I was - I was more - more interested in walking because - I c
ould sort of stop and have a look at something, where as with a bike you had to find somewhere to put the bike before you could look sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You didn't go fishing?
