nscious of the fact that - self help is a very useful thing. Sort of thing. You couldn't rely on other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 And they were very keen on education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Mother was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Did they try and teach you anything before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well I
 suppose yes, we did the sort of usual counting and A.B.C. and sort of thing. Oh yes, they used to - we used to have bricks - sort of cubes of - of wood with - pasted on them on one face'd be - capital A, on the other face would be a small a, and then per
h
aps on another there'd be a - a picture of an apple, or something of that sort, we used to play with as little kiddies, as babies. And - so we - we got the - A.B.C. into our heads. And then in counting I always remember we had - a - a board frame, well it
 
was really - a modernized abacus, with - you know wires across with beads on, coloured beads, and we used to - mostly - slide them across then slide them back but - mother would now and again get hold of us and - with a finger you know, that's three, that
's two and so on. And so we began to - all of us - most - both my sisters and myself - to - count and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Did you find that there was toys like that in other homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Yes, I think so, they were fairly common - they were fairly commo
n in the shops. So that they must have been in other homes. And then of course we'd - there were also - sort of kiddies books which were on the same style, a for apple, b for - butter or something of that sort you see, which we had as reading books as kid
dies. Mother would perhaps - sit with us and read - those to us.
