\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well - usual you know, the - from - the Anglo-Saxons upwards, dates and Kings an
d Queens and all that sort of thing which - of course is really a waste of time, I can never remember any of the dates now, except - 1066, and 1815. But - history was my - I suppose one of my best subjects, I always remember once having a lovely argument 
w
ith the master. He had made some statement in history and I knew he was wrong. But I had nothing to prove it so then - I know I went and dug out ell the history books I could find at home and borrowed two or three from the public library. The next history
 
lesson I carted them all to school. And - put them underneath my desk and of course he was recapping the previous lesson and he - made this same mistake and I put up me hand. He wanted to know what I wanted and I - corrected it. And he stuck to his argume
nt and so I gradually brought out each one of these books one after the other and quoted them, until I until I nearly got six for being - cheeky. But - that was - that was I suppose one of the things that I - I really did - really did enjoy history.

