 for a commission, so that if the salesman sold them he got an extra commission for those particular bits. And - of course there was always much reckoning up of spivs at the end of the week, so as to get - some of them used to get quite a g
ood bit of money. Of course there was not much - I mean, furniture was not expensive in those days by any means. Well it wasn't for a long while afterwards as far as that goes. But - of course there was a certain of amount of retail trade as well. Carpets
 and - lino. And that sort of thing. And then we opened a - they opened a - music department, well there always was a music department for pianos. And - they went in for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 gramophones}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 , and that's how we got our first musical instrument in the house. My own home. Was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  I bought there. A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  with a large tin horn. And - of course I used to borrow - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
 records over the weekend. Or at least we used to have them on like appro actually. Yes, from the shop. And - play them at home during the weekend and - perhaps if we liked one we might bay one, they used to cost half a crown then. And - then take them }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 back on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
 Monday morning you see. Of course the boss didn't know that - I was - the - the music salesman allowed me to - to do this. Well one o
f the managers, he - one of the head salesmen - he lived near us and he was the man I mentioned a while ago used to see going to work in a morning coat - frock coat. They were of course considered a little bit - up sort of thing. But - it was quite a - qu
i
te a good job. As a matter of fact - I - as I say, I quite enjoyed it and I learnt quite a lot there. As regards - ledger work and that sort of thing, but it was a - it was a dead end job, I don't say I would have stopped there long, it was a dead end job
 really.
