\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 When did you have to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh I used to have to 
be in about - I suppose half past nine, ten, you see. As a matter of fact of course after work one didn't go out much in the week. Perhaps Thursdays - at Thursday afternoons one might take myself off to the pictures, because of course then you could get i
nto the - the cinema for - sixpence. And one had a - cup of tea and biscuit thrown in. Besides seeing the - seeing the programme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 On Sundays you say you gave up going to Sunday school at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 So what might you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
Well, Sunday mornings I'd - sort of get up and have breakfast, get - dressed and I'd go out for a walk, perhaps - most - on most occasions go up onto the - there was the usual - most people in Woolwich go up onto the - garrison common, garrison parade 
ground and watch the parade going to - into church parade. Stop there until - they came out of church and marched off, then listen to the - the - Artillery }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 and who used to - play a few - marches and that sort of thing outside the officer's mess, an then g
o over at one o'clock to the - saluting battery and hear them fire the one o'clock gun, the time signal. Of course in between, while they were in church it was a case of - one strolled up and down amongst the crowd, a - a sort of - well the common express
i
on is a sort of monkey parade. You just strolled up - you might see somebody you knew, a neighbour or something of that sort and - sometimes my sisters'd be with me. I was never very pleased when they were as far as that goes. Well they were younger than 
me - but - it - that was the usual procedure, then come back to dinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You were in your suit for this were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes, I was always dressed up for that. Then in the afternoon - well - I don't suppose we did go out really. After tea - might go 
out in the evening, perhaps take - a stroll round or - stop at home and - just - sort of as one would - no sort of set - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 programmes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 . I very often perhaps would - walk down to the local - the market place and as I say listen to the - speakers down there, wander from one to the other. More amused than anything else at their words of wisdom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Were you taking more interest in politics after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh - oh no. No, no. No, no. It was - no, I suppose I - I don't think - really I altered much i
n ways, except of course I did - I had more freedom and - used to go out a bit more by myself you know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Why did they call it the monkey parade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well I don't know, it's a - it's a general term that has - because - it was - sort of wanderin
g backwards and forwards, you just paraded up and down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 By yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
I was by myself, but of course it was usually a case you wandered up and down by yourself until you saw somebody you - and you got off. Or picked up sort of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 I think the
 thing still - still exists, it's - it's a term that has been used - used in Woolwich I know in - whether it's a - a - an army term or not, or whether that was where it rose from I don't know, but I've always heard it in Woolwich as the monkey parade. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 I suppose it does really in all places where you got - crowds of - young people sort of just promenading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 There were usually groups of boys or groups of girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes, sometimes you'd get half a dozen girls all together and - half a d
ozen boys and - of course - they usually tried to - connect in some way or other. Drop a handkerchief or - something of that sort or - trip over. No, you don't have a wolf whistle in those days. Of course you got very - very - adventurous, perhaps you'd p
ull a girls hair or something of that sort, and then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 she\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
 turn round and - well it all depended who she was. She might give you a mouthful, she might be quite polite. But - it was a case of - you - you used some subterfuge to - you saw anybody you particul
arly liked. But - I don't know that I did really, I was not much a one for - it was not until after I was the Army that I got - interested in girls, and then I wasn't particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Usually at what sort of age did boys become interested in girls at that time?
\par 
