Oh - oh I suppose about fifteen, sixteen, seventeen. I don't know they didn't rally, I suppose you really only got - interested in girls because of course - it was a case of - marriage, I think there was no sort of - of taking a - a girl out
 - like you do now, sort of take her to the pictures and that - perhaps not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You didn't take them to the cinema then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh you did, but - only when you were - as the saying now is, going steady. You see, and - I mean you didn't start going steady
 until you got - very much older in most cases. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 
Because of course - well - one had to think about going steady, I mean people didn't - sort of get married until they were well in their twenties, late twenties, in their thirties actually, because of course 
you hadn't go the - the money and it was a case of having to save up - to - provide - find the where with all to - to get married on, you couldn't - well not in most cases could you - sort of get married as you can nowadays on the - never, never or hire p
urchases you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 I mean, hire purchase in those days was considered rather - rather - well not a nice thing, you didn't tell the neighbours you'd got it on hire purchase sort of thing.
