\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 That's rig
ht, you sort of - you - you really - it was most - I think most peoples; idea that - you should have - at least something - a home of some sort or other to - to offer - before you could - at least, the where with all to get it before you could sort of sta
rt thinking about - going steady with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Were there any other sort of obvious places apart from this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 monkey}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  parade where boys and girls could sort of meet who didn't know each other normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well only - churches and chapels and that sort o
f thing you see. There were no - there were - the - for meeting of - and of course the - a street, I mean - the girl next door and the neighbours girls and girls living a few - doors from you and that sort of thing, you'd naturally know those. And - there
 wouldn't - weren't - an extraordinary lot of - social opportunities, for really meeting girls, except as I say at church or - church functions or chapel functions or - something of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You had rather dropped those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes, I'd dropped out of all those really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Had you taken up any new clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
No. No. I - I hadn't actually, I used - used to keep myself then very much - rather to myself actually, a sort of a lone wolf sort of thing. I used to find much more - amusement in - watching the world go by really than - sort of going - going in with it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 More than when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes, more than when I was a schoolboy, yes. I used to spend a great deal of time reading at the library and that sort of thing 
as I - had - time and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You went to evening classes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 I did go to evening classes for a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 But - that didn't last long, I don't know why I dropped it really. I went for - shorthand -
 shorthand and book keeping. Well - I don't know quite why, I never got very far in shorthand. I can just about remember the alphabet of Pitmans, or most of it. But that's as far as I ever did get I think really. I don't know why I dropped - dropped night
 school 'cos I mean - really. I did, I gradually - I know I paid all fees and all that sort of thing but - not that they were a very great amount but - some - I don't know, I just - just dropped it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Would you make friends at a place like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well, yes, you could there you see. I mean, there you'd get somebody of the same sort of - you'd have something to - something in common.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 There was this friend who took you to a sort of literary evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes, I - I - I don't know who it was now
, I couldn't - I can't recall who on earth that was. I think it was somebody - it was before I left school actually I think. It might have been afterwards. But I haven't a foggiest notion who it was that - took me there, and I only went the once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 So there wasn't a sort of special chum or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
No, I had - no, no, not after I left school. When I was at school there was a boy on the opposite side of the road I used to spend a lot of time - time with in his house. He - him father had died and hi
s mother was - out a lot. And we used to spend - oh hours together in the - in the house. But - after I left school I think that dropped really. I suppose he'd got a job somewhere, I think he did, I think he left school about the same time as me. And - we
ll sort of just faded out really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You went over to his house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well I was more in his house than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 What sort of things did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh just - read or - played - played about, all sorts of thing and - usually - I was he used to make a - 
a very good welsh rarebit. And we used to tuck into that, very often make ourselves very bilious, but - I remember doing that quite often in the winter in his kitchen. Oh we used to get up to all sorts of - silly little things. No, that period - is really
 
a - a - between the time I left school and the time I joined the Army is really very - a dud period really, there was nothing much that I did at all - I used to again - go up to London, but then of course I'd - I could go up - not on my own two feet, I co
u
ld go on the train or - or the tram. And - I used to - sort of wander around. I was always a great one for - sort of wandering round the historical places of London, I used to know nearly all the back alleys for miles around really, of course they're most
l
y all gone now but - even now if I want to go from here to there in London I can usually - go quicker by doubling up the back alleys than I can by taking transport. But to tell - anybody how to get there I couldn't. Not - the way I would go you see. Or I'
d
 - another place we sometimes go to Greenwich Park, which was quite a good walk from us. There's usually - a band there on a Sunday evening. And - another monkey parade round the bandstand. Or Thursday evenings of course in the summer on Plumstead Common 
there was a - usually a band there. And - very often used to group there, perhaps sit on the grass or - wander round and round and round the - bandstand again you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5244319\charrsid15017164 It }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 was simple little things like that which really - you can't sort of - sort of pinpoint really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
When you went around in this suit and so on how did you feel when you saw some of the schoolboys that you'd been with who had got sort of labouring jobs and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh yes, well - as a matter of fact, again I can't remember meeting many 
of - the schoolboys who were in my class who left about the same time as me. We seemed to have got into - sort of separate compartments. I suppose if I ever did meet any of them we just passed the time of day and that sort of thing. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Sometimes we hear about scorn for somebody who's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 pen pusher}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
Ah yes. There was that sort of thing as I - going to say, but - as regards the schoolboys - if I met them - perhaps they were in the class below me when I left, well of course one used to - sort of f
eel very superior to them, they were mere schoolboys sort of thing. If a fellow was - just an ordinary labourer, well - there was again a sort of - feeling of - being superior, because you were white collar worker, he was a - a labourer or a - a mechanic 
or something of that sort. There was that - there was that feeling amongst everybody I think. That - white collar worker was a bit higher up. And - of course in the sort of labouring classes there were various degrees there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  But - no, as a matter of fact I 
can't remember really meeting many of - of boys who were at school with me, after I - after I left. I many have but - they never registered sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 I suppose this was a stage really when you felt most distant from your sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Yes. Yes.
 Yes. Because of course they were only - let's see, my two sisters were only about - my oldest sister was about ten I suppose, when I left school, yes, she was about four years difference. And of course - I was considering myself grown up when they were -
 
you know, beastly little nuisances. I know my youngest sister who was always - very keen on - on needlework - she would - she was always pinching my ties and cutting them up to make dolls clothes with, much to make my annoyance. And that sort of thing. Al
t
hough sometimes I used to - I used to help her to tell you the truth. I - often used to sit down and - sort of sketch out a - a dress and she'd make it for her dolls, and sometimes I used to even - sort of pin it together - pin the bits - make - make it m
yself, well at least get it pinned up together and cut it out and all the rest of it. I'm afraid it was that sort of - things that used to interest me more than - more than the sporting side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 That sister became the court dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Mm, the youngest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Was she a court dressmaker all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
No, she - well she was all her - practically all her working life until - oh I don't know - oh, until she got married, yes, she was a dressmaker right up until she got married. And then she gave 
up, but she still makes her own - dresses. But - yes, in the war - then of course - when war broke out - she - what the devil did she do during the war? During the last war. Oh yes, she went into - she went into the Civil Service in the last war. How on e
a
rth that - she managed it I don't know, but she was in the Labour Exchange. Right through, yes, right through the war. And then she married - she married after the war or before the war? After the war. No, before the war - before the war, yes, before the 
war. Yes - she was all - practically - well all her normal working life, put it that way, she was a court dressmaker in Hanover Square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 What does her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh he was - well - it just depends which one you mean, there was two of them. The fi
rst - the first one was - the son of a local - shopkeeper - who was - the business of - tools - tools and ironmongery and that sort of thing. He was - more mechanical than anything else. And then - she married again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 He worked in the shop did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
He worked in the shop sometimes and sometimes he worked outside, he was a bit of a ne'er do well actually, and - eventually she divorced him. And then she married again a - after the war - a fellow who - retired from - Colonial service. And they now live
 - he was a - oh a building inspector in charge of - of building some hospitals in Nigeria, and - he - they now live in Lancashire. But - she hasn't worked since - since then actually. Since the war. The eldest sister, well she - she was a secretary right
 
up to - well she married. She married first as a matter of fact, before I did. And - then - well she was at home as an ordinary housewife for a long while, then she - went out to - business as a secretary, and - eventually died. But - she was married - sh
e was the first one of the family to marry actually, and she married before - before I - well I was away in South Africa when she married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 He was - he was a gas - gas fitter, with the - what was then the South Metropolit
an Gas Company which is now of course the Gas Board. He's retired now and I don't know where he is. Down - somewhere in the - South - South West somewhere. But - they - they both did quite well and - we were, I suppose - yes. Yes. Yes, in the same street,
 
yes, and - after - of course we had grown up, I suppose we became much closer together than we had been when we were very much younger. Although I was never particularly - close to them because of course I was away from England - for so long while they we
re growing up. And - I was always a bit of a - a sort of - a loner really. You couldn't help it being - being away so - for so long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 But that is more a later time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Well, yes, right from - sort of outbreak of 1914 until 1928.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 When you were a boy you really did play a great deal with other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
Yes. Oh yes. Yes. No, well - no, I used to have spasms of it. Yes. Sometimes I used to - couldn't be bothered and another time I'd - enter into it sort of thing. But usually I had a sort of spar
e time job I suppose from about the time I was - about twelve I suppose really. Job of some sort or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 The newspaper round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Yes, the newspaper one and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10750940\charrsid15017164 grocers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid792229\charrsid15017164  and the greengrocers. Oh then there was another one I had for a little while, 
in a - in a - a drapers. That wasn't very long. Oh it was just keeping the shop tidy and delivering things. I wasn't very long in that, and I never liked that one because - the - shopkeeper there was - he was a very strict chapel merchant and was very - v
ery awkward - and - the whole atmosphere was not at all - to my liking and I didn't - I only had it for a - month or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Can you tell me more about it, what was wrong with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh I don't know, I suppose - he was a bit fussy. He was fussy and - ve
ry prim and proper. And - well he was - he was only a small shop really - he had been in a big shop and he'd - I suppose saved a bit of money and bought this small shop and he was just about - I should imagine - just about making a living out of it and th
at was all and consequently I never got much from him. And - one of the reasons why I didn't stop there very long, but I didn't like the man somehow. And - consequently I never sort of got down to it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 How did you get these jobs, were they advertised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
Well - yes, or you'd hear of them - through - somebody or other, oh Mr So and So wants a - somebody. And you'd - you know - and - perhaps mother would say, well you'd better go round and see him, or something of that sort. You'd just go round and - p
erhaps get taken on.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Do you remember how you found that first job in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 Oh the - the - what when I first - when I - went out properly? Oh from the local newspaper. That was advertised in the local newspaper.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13179849 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 You went round for an interview?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12126379 CV  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid792229\charrsid15017164 
Yes. It was - I found it on the Friday morning, the local newspaper came out on Friday, I saw it that morning, it was about a week after I'd left school. And I promptly - went down to then. I had an interview straight away and I started on
 the next Monday. So really I hadn't very much between leaving school and - starting work, only about a week which - was quite quick really. That's how I - that's how I got it.
\par }}